The paper discusses the use of deep learning, specifically siamese convolutional networks, to improve template matching by normalized cross correlation. This is a computer vision problem, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of deep learning models indicates that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of electron microscopy images, which suggests that it may belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the potential for generalization to other computer vision applications, which suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
